{"id":"b06f88ec05a40258714dedd2ebd89b05c014ab91","url":"https://fptalks.org/talks/fptalks26.html","title":"FPTalks 2026 — Thu Aug 6, free, online","site_name":"Info Flow","source":"Lobsters (技术社区)","byline":null,"excerpt":"Twelve ten-minute talks on the leading edge of floating-point research: Demmel, Zimmermann, Carson, and more. 8am–noon Pacific, free on Zoom, all talks recorded.","content_html":"<DIV class=\"page\" id=\"readability-page-1\"><p><em>Italicized entries are provisional topics; final titles to come.</em></p><div>\n      <h2> <time>7:50–8:00 PDT</time> Welcome</h2>\n\n      <h2><time>8:00–9:00 PDT</time> Session 1</h2>\n      \n      <section>\n\n        <h3>Correctly rounded functions: from pen-and-paper to formal proof</h3>\n        <p><a href=\"https://wonyeol.github.io/\">Wonyeol Lee</a> (POSTECH)\n           &amp; <a href=\"https://members.loria.fr/PZimmermann/\">Paul Zimmermann</a> (INRIA Nancy)</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n          <li><a href=\"https://core-math.gitlabpages.inria.fr/\">CORE-MATH</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://core-math.gitlabpages.inria.fr/sinh.pdf\">Example proof: sinh</a></li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h3><em>New results on FPANs and the SELTZO abstraction</em></h3>\n        <p><a href=\"https://www.dkzhang.com/\">David K Zhang</a>, Cerebras Systems</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n        </ul>\n\n        <h3>Golden models for numerical datapath</h3>\n        <p>Artem Yadrov, University of Utah</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n          <li><a href=\"https://github.com/pl-utah/zolotone\">Repo</a></li>\n        </ul>\n\n        <h3><em>Correctly rounded dot products</em></h3>\n        <p>Sehyeok Park, Rutgers University</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n        </ul>\n\n      </section>\n\n      <h2><time>9:00–9:30 PDT</time> Break</h2>\n\n     