 Sensitivity Analysis</h3>\n        <p><a href=\"https://www.cs.cornell.edu/~bindel/\">David Bindel</a>, Cornell</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n        </ul>\n\n        <h3><em>Title to be announced</em></h3>\n        <p><a href=\"https://wsmoses.com\">William S. Moses</a>, UIUC</p>\n        <ul>\n          <!-- <li><a href=\"\">Recording</a></li> -->\n        </ul>\n\n      </section>\n\n      <h2><time>12:00–12:10 PDT</time> Conclusion</h2>\n    </div></DIV>","content_text":"Italicized entries are provisional topics; final titles to come. 7:50–8:00 PDT Welcome 8:00–9:00 PDT Session 1 Correctly rounded functions: from pen-and-paper to formal proof Wonyeol Lee (POSTECH) & Paul Zimmermann (INRIA Nancy) CORE-MATH Example proof: sinh New results on FPANs and the SELTZO abstraction David K Zhang, Cerebras Systems Golden models for numerical datapath Artem Yadrov, University of Utah Repo Correctly rounded dot products Sehyeok Park, Rutgers University 9:00–9:30 PDT Break 9:30–10:30 PDT Session 2 IEEE P3109 update Andrew Fitzgibbon, Graphcore NVFP4 pre-training Paul Gibbons, NVIDIA Direction-Preserving Number Representations Bardia Zadeh, Imperial College London Paper Repo Demo Range Analysis of Neural Surfaces Nick Sharp, NVIDIA Project page 10:30–11:00 PDT Break 11:00–12:00 PDT Session 3 Grading the BLAS Jim Demmel, UC Berkeley High Accuracy with Low Precision Erin Carson, Charles University Adjoints for Roundoff Sensitivity Analysis David Bindel, Cornell Title to be announced William S. Moses, UIUC 12:00–12:10 PDT Conclusion","fetched_at":"2026-07-22T14:44:48.707Z","ok":true,"blocks":[{"html_en":"<p><em>Italicized entries are provisional topics; final titles to come.</em></p>","sentences":[{"en":"Italicized entries are provisional topics; final titles to come.","zh":"斜体条目是临时主题；最终冠军即将到来。"}]},{"html_en":"<h2> <time>7:50–8:00 PDT</time> Welcome</h2>","sentences":[{"en":"7:50–8:00 PDT Welcome","zh":"7:50–8:00 PDT 欢迎"}]},{"html_en"